-- Weiss Starts PivotalPoint, Fisher Joins Jennings, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-10-18T18:13:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-18/weiss-starts-pivotalpoint-fisher-joins-jennings-vlaad-says.html
 Lindsay Weiss launched PivotalPoint
Advisory Group after leaving Dundee Securities Corp., according
to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based financial services recruiting
firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * Jennings Capital Inc. hired Doug Van Peteghem and Tim Fisher
from Stonecap Securities Inc. and David Lawson.  * Todd Papau joined Northleaf Capital Partners Ltd. as vice
president, sales and business development, based in Toronto.
Papau was previously at Goldman Sachs Group Inc.  * Former UBS AG mining and metals investment banking director
Steven Velimirovic moved to head the metals and mining Americas
team at Societe Generale.  * Craig Hiddleston joined Grafton Asset Management Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
 edmitrieva1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
